ce:section.ce:para:
The surface composition of the hybrid materials was analyzed by XPS. As given in Fig. 4a, the XPS spectra for various samples indicated the presence of Mg, Al, C, O, N, and Pd elements. As deposited in Fig. 5
                        , the high-resolution XPS spectra display that the binding energies of Mg 2p, Al 2p, S 2p, C 1s, N 1s, and O 1s are at 49.5, 74.1, 163.5, 285.6, 399.4, and 538.7 eV, respectively (Li et al., 2020). It can be found that the peak intensity and content of N 1s increased sequentially after PDA modification, polymer PNIPAM grafting, and CDs/palladium loading (Fig. 5 and Table 1
                        ), indicating that both PNIPAM and CDs were supported on the LDH surface, and LDH@PDA@PNIPAM@Pd/CDs hybrid material was successfully synthesized. Fig. 4b-d show the high-resolution C 1s, N 1s and Pd 3d spectra of LDH@PDA@PNIPAM@Pd/CDs. The signal peaks at 284.5, 285.7 and 288.1 eV of C 1s are attributable to the C=C/C-C, CN, and O-C=O bonds (Essner et al., 2015). The two types peaks at 399.2 and 400.0 eV of N 1s are related to the NH- and -N = groups, respectively, revealing the presence of CDs onto LDH@PDA@PNIPAM@Pd/CDs. Besides, two sharp Pd signals at 335.4 and 340.7 eV are ascribed to Pd 3d5/2 and Pd 3d3/2, respectively, which proved that Pd NPs have been successfully loaded on the surface of LDH@PDA@PNIPAM (Zhou et al., 2018). Surprisingly, two peaks attributed to Pd2+ (337.4 and 343.1 eV) can be observed in the materials, and the content of Pd2+ was relatively not low. The existence of Pd2+ may originate from three aspects: it may come from unreduced Pd2+ adsorbed on the surface of the sample; PdO may be formed by exposure to air during synthesis and storage (Gracia-Espino et al., 2014; Zhou et al., 2018); It is also possible to form ultra-small palladium clusters (Rossell et al., 2016).
